						               													<description>Uniqe tactical card game with three different versions for youngsters and adults!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your goal in the game is to compile the most valuable collection of treasures in your treasure chest, gaining the most points. You can collect most points if you have a card in your treasure chest, that no one else has, not even the Bank or if you collect many of the same type of cards, and the Bank also has many of them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game includes:&amp;#10;5 types of treasure cards, each with 3 categories, slightly different from one another&amp;#10;3 types of markers:&amp;#10;Red marker: you have to throw out cards permanently&amp;#10;Green marker: you give the card to the Bank&amp;#10;Boat marker: you make the card part of your treasure chest&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game overview:&amp;#10;In the beginning of the game the card pile is divided equally between the players. The first player turn their top card face up and put down without looking at it. As soon as the card is shown anyone can put one of their markers on the card. One card can only have one marker. The round is over when all the players showed the defined number of cards (for example 3 players show 4 cards per person in a round). Cards without markers are used again in the last round, the marked cards are placed according to their marking. The game is over when all the cards are played out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scoring:&amp;#10;If you have a card that is not in the Bank, but more than one player has it, is worth 1 point per card. &amp;#10;If you have a card that is also can be found in the Bank, the card will be worth as many points as the number of cards in the Bank.&amp;#10;If you have a card that is not in the Bank, and only one player has it, is worth 10 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
